President Trump expressed his condolences for the victims of the recent shooting in Pensacola, Florida, and mentioned that King Salman of Saudi Arabia called to offer his sympathies. He also discussed the strong state of the US economy, citing record-setting job numbers, low unemployment rates, and growth in various sectors. The President highlighted the administration's efforts to eliminate job-killing regulations and promote economic prosperity. Several business leaders shared their experiences and concerns, including the need for regulatory reform and support for small businesses. Secretary of Transportation Elaine Chao discussed infrastructure and regulatory issues, while Secretary of Labor Gene Scalia praised the administration's policies for contributing to job growth and wage increases. The President also mentioned the positive impact of tariffs on the steel industry and the need for improvements in air traffic control and the commercial space industry. The meeting concluded with President Trump thanking the participants and expressing optimism for the future of the US economy.